"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.5.3.1\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.5.3.1</span> Thread, string, yarn</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">חוּט</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(chut)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:23\">GEN 14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:18\">JOS 2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:12\">JDG 16:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:12\">ECC 4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:3\">SNG 4:3</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">פָּתִיל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(pathil)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:18\">GEN 38:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:25\">GEN 38:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:28\">EXO 28:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:37\">EXO 28:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:3\">EXO 39:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:21\">EXO 39:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:31\">EXO 39:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:38\">NUM 15:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:15\">NUM 19:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:9\">JDG 16:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:3\">EZK 40:3</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/OAI-0015_piece_string.png\" alt=\"A piece of string\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">A piece of string (Image generated by ChatGPT using OpenAI technology)</figcaption></figure>Thread or yarn for weaving was made by twisting fibers on a spindle (see <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.5.3 Cloth manufacture&lt;REALIA:1.5.3&gt;</a>). A single strand of thread made in this way was not particularly strong, but cloth made by interweaving many of these thin strands together was strong enough for many uses. See also <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.14 Rope, cord&lt;REALIA:1.14&gt;</a>.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The essential difference between “thread” or “string” and “cord” or “rope” was less in its thickness than in its composition. A rope or cord was made of two or more single strands twisted or braided together. All the occurrences of the Hebrew word <em>pathil</em> are listed here, but in one or two of the passages the translator may consider that a heavier cord is intended.</p>\n<p>In <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:3\">EXO 39:3</a> the Hebrew word <em>pathil</em> is used to refer to fine “threads” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr>, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr>) or “strands” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr>) made of gold. Some languages may have a separate word for such a “filament” made of metal.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
